OL,4,CInquiry amid special advocate request
OL,6,F"Everybody thinks that the inquiry is
OL,7,Fcapable of doing a good job. Everybody
OL,8,Fthinks the counsel to the inquiry are
OL,9,Fexperienced in this field. Everybody
OL,10,Fthinks they're very well qualified.
OL,11,FEverybody thinks they're very
OL,12,Fdiligent, but we need the second tier
OL,13,Fof representation," he added.
OL,15,F"Everyone recognises that large key
OL,16,Fparts of this process are likely to be
OL,17,Fclosed .... it's frustrating for the
OL,18,Findividuals, because they want to know
OL,19,Fthe truth. They want to know that
OL,20,Fwhatever findings may be made are
OL,21,Freliable.
