OL,6,F"They view a special advocate not as
OL,7,Fsome special bonus or as a challenge
OL,8,Fto the inquiry legal team but as
OL,9,Fsomething that should be granted as
OL,10,Fthey see it, as an additional
OL,11,Fassistance to them in shining light on
OL,12,Fany material which is withheld as
OL,13,Fclosed by the state authorities.
OL,15,F"They have that legitimate interest we
OL,16,Fsay, and that certainly is a matter of
OL,17,Fnot only public confidence but in
OL,18,Fparticular the confidence of the
OL,19,Ffamilies."
