OL,3,CConfidence risk in Omagh Bombing
OL,4,CInquiry amid special advocate request
OL,6,F"Why do you tell me that every single
OL,7,Fdocument, piece of information needs
OL,8,Fto be placed into the open," the chair
OL,9,Fasked.
OL,11,FMr McAleer responded saying they
OL,12,Frespect the powers and the processes
OL,13,Fof the inquiry, but they wanted to
OL,14,Freflect the effect of scepticism based
OL,15,Fon the experience of the core
OL,16,Fparticipants.
OL,18,F"The series of revelations over the
OL,19,Fyears since the bomb have served to
OL,20,Fundermine their trust in the state,"
OL,21,Fhe added.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@\O]zD@AOU|D@dO]
